race.description: Gorski Hardox Tough Tippers 5Th Grade F
race.comment: COUSIN HENRY (2) skirted wide from an outside draw last start and found the front, leading throughout to win (18.90) at this track in a Grade 5 over 350m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. BORN TO RACE (8) finished in the placings last time but could not have been more impressive before that in his convincing 18.78 win at this track over 350m. Expected to feature on best figures. BOGIE BECKER (1) placed last time (18.92) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 2 lengths. Has already won out of this draw. Looks one of the chances. FEARLESS FREAK (6) was in the money again last time and not beaten far when second (19.00) at this track in a Grade 5.
